## Useful Docker Commands

View running containers:

```bash
docker ps
```

View app logs:

```bash
docker logs {{ slug }}
```

Restart project:

```bash
cd {{ project_path }}
docker compose restart
```

Stop project:

```bash
cd {{ project_path }}
docker compose down
```

Start project:

```bash
cd {{ project_path }}
docker compose up -d
```

## Cloudflare

If automatic Cloudflare setup was not used, add a published application route that points to:

```text
http://{{ local_base_url_host }}:{{ port }}
```

## Error 1033 Troubleshooting

If you see Cloudflare Error 1033, the tunnel DNS record exists but Cloudflare cannot currently resolve the tunnel connection.

Check the tunnel container on the NAS:

```bash
sudo docker ps
sudo docker ps -a
```

If cloudflared is stopped, start it:

```bash
sudo docker start cloudflared
```
